  "label": "Aurorashade Sleep Cell",
  "description": "Aurorashade Sleep Cell is a pressure-tight sleeping compartment set along the hab’s narrow run of chambers, its soot-scored basaltcrete panels broken by service conduits and gasketed seams. A low bunk frame and wall-anchored locker define the space, with fold-down fittings designed to withstand vibration and intermittent power loss. Shielded lumen strips maintain a cold, uniform light, while lead-lined shutters and dust-burdened vents blunt the bruise-colored auroral glare and constant ash infiltration characteristic of Vespera Tertius.",
